<article id="node-15883">
<h1 >6.3.4 Retirement &amp; Widows Overpayments</h1>
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>This section contains information on overpayment of <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#age" title="Age pension">Age</a> and <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#wp" title="Wife pension">WP</a> related to <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#dva" title="Department of Veterans' Affairs">DVA</a> 'double dipping'.</p>
<h2>DVA 'double dipping' overpayment - Age &amp; WP</h2>
<p>A person cannot receive a service pension from DVA and a social security pension at the same time. Should DVA be unable to cease a service pension by the grant date of a social security pension then they will calculate an overpayment and advise Centrelink.</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 23(1)-'social security pension'</p>
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/4/1">3.4.1</a> Age - Qualification &amp; Payability, <a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/4/2">3.4.2</a> WP - Qualification &amp; Payability</p>
</div>
</article>	<div id="view-last-reviewed-date">
		
		  
